Jeff,
We need to document an important operational update that affects support an=
d the transition.
1) Access status / operational update
As of last night, our team no longer has administrative access to key syste=
ms in the environment. Specifically, our remote tools appear to have been r=
emoved, our access account is disabled, and RDP/administrative access to th=
e AD servers is not available. As a result, Technijian is currently blocked=
 from performing troubleshooting or remediation actions on those systems wi=
thout restored access and a coordinated plan with TechHeights.
To avoid conflicting changes during transition, please confirm today:

  *   that TechHeights is now the primary administrator for remediation goi=
ng forward; and
  *   the authorized TechHeights recipients (names/emails) who are approved=
 to receive Boston Group administrator credentials.

2) April invoices issued and open balances
The April 1 invoices have been issued, and the following invoices remain op=
en/pending payment:
Past due (3/31/2026):
=95 Invoice #27890 (Recurring) =96 $552.00 =96 Due 3/31/2026
=95 Invoice #27949 (Monthly Support) =96 $5,645.35 =96 Due 3/31/2026
Due 4/30/2026:
=95 Invoice #28064 (Service Cancellation) =96 $126,442.50 =96 Due 4/30/2026
Issued 4/1/2026; due 5/1/2026:
=95 Invoice #28112 (Recurring) =96 $552.00 =96 Due 5/1/2026
=95 Invoice #28143 (Monthly Support) =96 $5,694.60 =96 Due 5/1/2026
Please reply with the expected remittance date for the outstanding balances=
 (or a proposed payment arrangement), so we can complete closeout.
3) Counsel review / coordination
You previously noted your attorney would be reviewing the agreement. To str=
eamline this, please have your counsel propose a few available times for a =
counsel-to-counsel call (Technijian counsel is cc=92d) to review the cancel=
lation charge methodology and the outstanding invoices through the terminat=
ion period.
Separately, if you would like to proceed with the previously discussed glob=
al settlement option for the cancellation charge, please confirm in writing=
 and we will document it accordingly.

Thank you,

[Ravi Jain]
